node.text:
I recently started following this bomb.com self help coach on my personal Instagram account. @therealjoirizarry 

Her daily convos/advice/ viewpoints are spot on in this stage of growth and healing. 

This particular post resonates with me as I started setting hella boundaries. Now I can identify that empty feeling, the loss that she speaks of. Maybe you can relate?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by A Safe Place Inside Your Head in Austin, Texas. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Kira J @lamKiraJ QបL Y'all be beating yourself up about the mistakes you've made in the past as if you been here twice or something. This is your first time living this life. Give yourself some grace as you've learned to navigate through it. You don't know what you don't know til you know better.'.

node.text:
It’s hard to give yourself grace when you mess up. It’s had to say it’s ok, when you’ve failed at something you wanted to succeed at. 

Mistakes are proof that you are trying. Mistakes are not failures but steps to success. 

Now if you keep making the same mistake over and over, that’s on you. But trying and failing, or stumbling, it’s all part of the steps that we take in this dance called living. - @therealjoirizarry 

“I’m not perfect, but I’m always real”  @2pac 

📸 @iamkiraj on Twitter 
.
.
.
.
.
#giveyourselfgrace #falldown7getup8 #lifesadance🌻💛 #beyoueveryoneelseistaken #theresnoonelikeyouandthatsyoursuperpower #imakemistakeseveryday #learningasigo #mentalhealthmemes🖤 #thisonelife✨ #babysteps #mentalhealthawareness #safeplaceinsideyourhead

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by A Safe Place Inside Your Head in Austin, Texas. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Instagram allows you to be social while still being antisocial. That shit is beautiful'.

node.text:
Today I’m feeling especially antisocial. 

Being able to distance my self physically but still being socially active in my own cocoon is the shit. 

I’m sure this behavior isn’t great for my mental health, but I’m gonna do it anyway, just for today. 

Some days I need physical space from peopling, and today I will honor it. - @therealjoirizarry 
.
.
.
.
.
#perfectlonely #ineedsomespace #itstoopeopleyoutthere #anxietyproblems #sociallydistant #physicallydistant #givemesomespace #extrovertedintrovert #sundayfunday #mentalhealthmemes🖤 #asafeplaceinsideyourhead

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by A Safe Place Inside Your Head in Austin, Texas with @realpettymay0. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text:
You do you, boo. 

I was thinking today about some of the weird shit I do to help MYSELF work through mental health issues that work for me. 

I talk to myself…. a lot. And music is my magic place to quickly change my mood, in so many directions. And when my brain feels like it’s on fire, ASMR on YouTube helps calm me down. - @therealjoirizarry 

Drop down below a method you use to deal with your mental health issues 👇🏼

 📸 @realpettymay0 
.
.
.
.
.

May be a Twitter screenshot of 2 people and text that says 'Joyce @itsladyjoyce social anxiety is the only reason why I don't cry in public, my fear of being noticed is stronger than my need to release emotion. 5:06 AM 6/21/19 Twitter for Android'.

node.text:
Or a funerals or at weddings or in general basically. 

What if someone sees me?? 

Crying when I’m alone is another story. It’s a fill on boo hoo sob fest. 

Surely I’m not the only one who cry’s alone? - @therealjoirizarry 

📸 @itsladyjoice on Twitter 
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
TW: Suicide 

In this interview with Julie from @meindstories I talked about my brothers death and my own struggles growing up as a kid. This was a really difficult interview because we touched on some really emotional things I haven’t unpacked in a while. I’m going to post a link to the video in my stories but she was an awesome interviewer and I definitely love her mission. Also shout out to the @twelveriversproductions team for being great host. Please reach out if you ever need love and support. - @tanner_hamilton22 
.
.
.
.
.
.
#suicideawarenessmonth #suicideprevention #suicidepreventionmonth #suicideawarness #nationalsuicidepreventionday #asafeplaceinsideyourhead #keepgoing #youareenough #youarenotalone #weareproudofyou

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by A Safe Place Inside Your Head in Austin, Texas with @tanner_hamilton22, @atxlien, and @therealjoirizarry. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text:
This is what depression and anxiety looks like. This picture was taken one week before my son Kenneth Thomas Gaskin, Jr. 1984-2009 RIP died by suicide, 11 years ago. He is the inspiration for @asafeplaceinsideyourhead 
.
.
.
Mental health awareness and suicide prevention shouldn’t need a special day, it’s what we should work on every day.  If you know someone who seems struggling or if you’re struggling, reach out and say “R U Okay?” Or say to someone, “I’m not ok “. 
.
.
If you want to join a closed Facebook group designed for open discussions on mental health issues join A Safe Place Inside your Head and we’re here for you! - @therealjoirizarry  @tanner_hamilton22  @atxlien 

#worldsuicidepreventionday #suicideprevention #suicideawarness #stopsuicide #endthestigma #areyouokay #areyouok #mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealthadvocate #safeplaceinsideyourhead

May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Aya @AyaReina Friendly reminder that suicide prevention isn't just saying "here if you need to talk!" and posting a hotline number. it's healthcare. it's housing. it's adequate social welfare. it's food security. it's actually being able to access mental health services quickly. 1:20 1:20AM-9/9/21-TwitterWebApp AM 9/9/21 Twitter Web'.

node.text:
During #suicideawarenessmonth this is most important. Advocating for the right for everyone to have the ability to get mental health support quickly regardless of financial status. Having better options for both providers and patients because I’m a firm believer that if we pay therapist and psychiatrist their worth WHILE providing low cost or free mental healthcare we all win. We save lives, we don’t leave anyone behind and most importantly we help people live their most authentic lives. This is a collective effort we must have from society because I look at all my fellow people and see so many suffering that can’t get help. Me and my mom created this account/ nonprofit to change the narrative on mental health and to normalize conversations about very difficult topics and we are just getting started. We hope you have enjoyed the journey and stick around for the change we want to see in the world. - @tanner_hamilton22 
.
.
.
.
.
📸= AyaReina on Twitter
.
.
.
#suicideawarenessmonth #asafeplaceinsideyourhead #howcanwehelp #youareamazing #keepgoing #pleasekeepfighting #suicideprevention #suicideawarness #depression #anxiety

May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Tweet Viral Tweets Pain Depression & Anxiety @ILLUMINUSNUMB "ur so polite" thank i was raised in constant fear of upsetting people 9:26 PM 9/8/21 Twitter for iPhone 12.1K Retweets 492 Quote Tweets 49K Likes'.

node.text:
This 100%, I am so scared of upsetting people that it’s made me a perfectionist with anxiety. I always feel like I’m forgetting something to the point I start overthinking and overanalyzing situations and in which I end up hurting my own feelings. Anyone else feel this way lol? - @tanner_hamilton22 
.

May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Viral Tweets Jaron Myers @jaronmyers We're all so emotionally damaged from this last year and a half that Steve from Blue's Clues was like" have to address the nation" 11:47AM AM 9/8/21 Twitter for iPhone 25.2K Retweets 608 Quote Tweets 149K Likes'.

node.text:
This made me laugh so hard, I swear I needed that closure from Steve and I’m glad I got it. Maybe he can close the time rift if what’s been a crazy year….emotionally I’ve grown because I’ve had too. Navigating the waters of these last 2-3 years has been hard for everyone but I’m proud of you for continuing to keep going. Have a beautiful day. - @tanner_hamilton22 
.

node.text:
I needed this today, maybe someone you know needs it too. You are amazing, and whatever you do today I hope you do it the best you can. Even if you take a day off from society, it’s okay you can always start tomorrow. Grind culture can be toxic sometimes. Take care of yourself. - @tanner_hamilton22
